Upgraded Russian helicopter gunship card-52M first released at the end of the year - Xinhua Network
On the basis of plans by the Russian Ministry of Defence, an upgraded version of the Russian helicopter gunship (hereinafter called Wutai) card-52M will be completed for the first time in December of this year to replace and leave the plant, and the model will be significantly improved in terms of reconnaissance, communications and weapons performance.
According to a recent Russian newspaper, the development contract for Wutaka-52M, known as the “Super Short-Skissed Crocodile”, was signed last April by the Russian military and military engineering units, and the first two such upgrades are currently being modified at the Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of the Russian Aerospace Corporation Progress Group, whose national testing and upgrading will be completed by October 2022.
According to Russian experts who are aware of the above-mentioned upgrades, the “presence” of the “Super Short-Sniffing Crocodile” — the Wu Nacca-52 — was formally installed in November 2011 and the model was exposed to some weaknesses in its use, the purpose of which was to upgrade the “clipboard”.
It was reported that, compared to card-52, the card-52M would partially use new, non-weighted protective materials, its pilot cabins would be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to withstand missile attacks, thereby increasing the probability of survival on the battlefield; more powerful generators would be assembled to provide electricity for more sophisticated on-board electronic equipment; the photovoltaic system would be upgraded to enable the detection and identification of more distant battlefield targets; new light multi-purpose missiles with a major attack on armoured combat vehicles and concrete fortifications, with a range of up to 20 kilometres, would increase approximately one-fold the range of missiles of the same type as those in active Russian military use; and their defensive weapons and communications equipment would be used to maximize their utility with Mi-28NM armed helicopters capable of attacking air targets, thus making the associated maintenance simple and economical.
In addition, card-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapons targeting systems and navigation equipment.
The Russian experts also stated that it was of concern that the card-52M would be equipped with communications equipment to communicate with drones, thus providing real-time air access to information transmitted by nearby drones, such as showing images taken by drones on the cabin screen of the helicopter.
It is planned that the pilots of the card-52M will be able to directly manipulate the drones with which they work, thereby improving their knowledge of the situation on the battlefield and their guidance on long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, the Deputy Minister of Defence of the Russian Federation, Krivorochko, stated last December that the Ministry of Defence plans to purchase more than 110 VK-52M by 2027.
