The 26-day-lined Tunnel of the Three Isthmus, which is a full-line control project for Zheng Manghai, is located along the border between Phuong Dynasty County and Wakayama County in Chongqing City, approximately 18.9 km long and 890 metres deep.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and was fully operational on 26 July 2020.
According to the Royal Army, which is responsible for the design of the China-China Iron II Engineering Group limited liability company, Zheng Wangau Tun Tunnel, the location of the Tunnels in the small three canyons is very difficult to design and construct because they are exposed to the risks of rock solubility, mudslides and massive deformations of soft rock, which are of high risk to class I.
“In the course of project construction, we have adopted special designs for more than 30 types of dissolved holes, using advanced geological forecasts such as geological surveying, physical exploration and hyper-prevalence drilling. For example, a 24-metre bridge is designed to avoid the fall of a tunnel by crossing a large dissolved hole of more than 10 metres vertical length and 55 metres deep inside the tunnel.” The Royal Army says.
